@Barry Ancona - it is odd to me that so many people think the entire external world should conform to their own understanding of things, rather than accept that there are other ways of viewing such things. Hence the insistence that it is just wrong to claim that TAMALE is a word in English now. I do wish Dan good luck in his quest to change the entire world's understanding of the word to conform to his own. 

I have my own little quirks, most famously that "octopi" is a shudder-worthy plural of "octopus." I would never use it and I insist that my marine bio student not use it. (No marine biologist uses it so I must teach them how language is used within our discipline.) But I don't expect the entire planet to conform to my own peculiar take on this. I accept that "octopi" is out there and that it is fair game for a crossword. 

*sigh*
